step_data.thought:
I can see from the page accessibility tree that I'm now back on the Customers listing page. I notice there's a success message: 'You saved the customer.' This confirms that the new customer (John Doe with email john.doe123@example.com) has been successfully added to the Magento Admin Panel.

The customer listing should now include the newly added customer, but I notice there's a filter applied for ZIP: 75201 (as shown in the Active filters section), which might be why we see '0 records found' if our new customer doesn't have that ZIP code. However, since our task was simply to add a new customer, and we've received confirmation that the customer was saved successfully, we have completed the requested task.

I should inform the user that the task has been completed successfully.
step_data.action: stop('I have successfully added a new customer named John Doe with email john.doe123@example.com to the Magento Admin Panel. The system has confirmed with the message "You saved the customer."')
